<dl id="n11054k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11054k">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11054k"> 54(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> usual between man &amp; wife ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Vaquier. / Three Statements Read in Court. / Dramatic Denials.<font color="green">[...]</font> Mr. Jones &amp; Vaquier</b> <font color="green">[...]</font> Jean Pierre Vaquier, the Frenchman, appeared yesterday for the fifth time before the Woking Bench, charged on remand with the murder of Mr. Alfred Poynter Jones, landlord of the Blue Anchor Hotel, Byfleet. It is alleged that strychnine was placed in a bottle of salts used by Mr. Jones.<font color="green">[...]</font> Mr. Ernest George Whitewick, of the Green, New Malden, Surrey, who was manager of the Blue Anchor from August 1923, when Mr. Jones took over the licence, gave evidence. / Mr. H.D. Roome: As to the domestic life of Mr. and Mrs. Jones, on what terms were they? &mdash;Very friendly in the <mark>usual way of man and wife</mark>.<font color="green">[...]</font> <b>Acts of Familiarity.</b> <font color="green">[...]</font><mark>How did Vaquer and Mrs. Jones converse?mdash;With the aid of a dictionary</mark>. <small> <a name="DM27may24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DM27may24"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (27 May 1924) 10/1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
